post_text: The 2020 Putnam County Fair has NOT been canceled. We are continuing to plan for a fantastic 2020 fair. The Fair Board will continue to work with the Putnam County Health Department and the City Council to ensure that safety is a top priority. We will continue to watch the state recommendations and make sure that we are able to comply with any restrictions. If a decision is made, we will be sure to keep you updated here.

post_text:
COVID-19 UPDATE:

Right now we are proceeding with the 2020 Putnam County Fair as scheduled. The Fairboard is working hard to bring you another year of great shows, entertainment and food. We will continue to work together with the Putnam County Health Department to ensure that we are in compliance with any COVID related policies.

We are aware that many events are cancelling, but as more restrictions are being lifted we feel that timing is on our side with such a late summer event.

If you have any questions, please feel free to message us here or contact a Fairboard member.

Thank you to our Grand Champion Sponsor, The Putnam County Health Department! The Health Department provides a broad range of help and services to people all over Putnam County!

Stop by their booth at this years fair & be sure to check out the driving simulator from 10AM-3PM on Friday sponsored by the Putnam County Health Department & The NWMO Roadway Safety Coalition.
